00:14:54,827 --> 00:14:57,137
or out in your neighborhood
boosting car stereos?

255
00:14:57,196 --> 00:14:58,834
No, here, definitely.

256
00:15:00,032 --> 00:15:02,842
Hey, Frankie, Ruthie's Jerk
Palace is coming in at 4:00, huh?

257
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:04,472
You want to set up the board?

258
00:15:05,171 --> 00:15:07,014
I got a restaurant commercial to do.

259
00:15:08,441 --> 00:15:11,979
You must do a lot of these commercials
to pay for all this gear.

260
00:15:12,044 --> 00:15:16,390
Oh, commercials, demos. I even got a
couple of clients get on the Latin charts.

261
00:15:17,717 --> 00:15:19,697
Is Frankie one of your success stories?

262
00:15:20,119 --> 00:15:22,258
Frankie's like an apprentice, you know?

263
00:15:22,321 --> 00:15:25,268
Another couple of years, he'll know
enough to open his own studio.

264
00:15:25,324 --> 00:15:28,601
So he gets his own studio,
and then there's Sami.

265
00:15:28,728 --> 00:15:30,207
What happened with him?

266
00:15:34,634 --> 00:15:36,875
He was a victim of his father's impulses.

267
00:15:37,236 --> 00:15:39,876
The man was an ex-convict.
That was his nature.

268
00:15:40,373 --> 00:15:43,183
He was probably mixed up
with some bad people,

269
00:15:43,242 --> 00:15:44,550
and the poor kid paid the price.

270
00:15:45,511 --> 00:15:47,184
You know, one last thing,

271
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:51,023
before we let you get on with
your, you know, commercial.

272
00:15:51,918 --> 00:15:53,090
Jamal Dupuis,

273
00:15:54,921 --> 00:15:57,197
did he hang out here with Sami?

274
00:15:57,256 --> 00:16:01,068
Yeah, for a while. But I think the
kid moved out of the neighborhood.

275
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:04,138
That's what we heard.

276
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:07,044
Well, thanks.

277
00:16:07,667 --> 00:16:08,771
ELECTRONIC VOICE: Baby!

278
00:16:08,835 --> 00:16:11,748
(CHUCKLING)
I really like... I really like that.

279
00:16:16,542 --> 00:16:18,783
Jamal moved down to the barrier islands,

280
00:16:19,378 --> 00:16:21,790
to live with his father in South Carolina.

281
00:16:21,848 --> 00:16:23,850
EAMES: Why? Was he having problems here?

282
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:28,058
He wanted to work, and they don't
let 13-year-olds work up here.

283
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:33,360
So, they say you can make good
money crabbing down there.

284
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:35,129
Have you talked to him lately?

285
00:16:35,194 --> 00:16:37,936
He calls from time to time from pay phones.

286
00:16:38,431 --> 00:16:40,411
His father doesn't have a phone now.

287
00:16:40,466 --> 00:16:43,310
Have you told him what
happened to his friend Sami?

288
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:45,571
No.

289
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,413
Well, they were best friends.

290
00:16:48,474 --> 00:16:51,353
They hung out together at the
sound studio on Bergen Street.

291
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:55,782
We have nothing to say against Mr. Rios.

292
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,526
Your daughter is very cute.

293
00:17:03,155 --> 00:17:05,465
You're happy Jamal's out of the house.

294
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:11,105
Why would you say that?

295
00:17:11,531 --> 00:17:14,137
Well, you don't have any photos of him.

296
00:17:16,802 --> 00:17:19,442
What's the town where Jamal's
staying with his father?

297
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,076
It's not just one town.

298
00:17:22,742 --> 00:17:26,189
Well, his father's got family on
a lot of the islands down there,

299
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:28,222
so Jamal stays with them, too.

300
00:17:29,315 --> 00:17:32,762
My favorite place down there
is Gullah Gullah Island.

301
00:17:32,818 --> 00:17:35,628
I bet Jamal probably goes crabbing there.

302
00:17:35,688 --> 00:17:37,497
Oh, yes. I remember him telling me that.

303
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:40,333
Telling you that he went crabbing
on Gullah Gullah Island?

304
00:17:44,196 --> 00:17:49,077
You know, Mrs. Dupuis, there
is no island with that name.

305
00:17:51,604 --> 00:17:53,641
Well, I'm sure I heard of it.

306
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:56,916
That's because

307
00:17:59,679 --> 00:18:02,785
there's a children's television
show called Gullah, Gullah Island,

308
00:18:02,848 --> 00:18:06,295
and you probably watched it with
him when he was growing up.

309
00:18:10,122 --> 00:18:11,465
(SOBBING)

310
00:18:14,460 --> 00:18:15,905
Where is he?

311
00:18:16,896 --> 00:18:18,603
What happened to him?

312
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:23,807
He's with his father, and you have to go now.

313
00:18:23,903 --> 00:18:26,509
Mr. Dupuis, we can protect your family.

314
00:18:28,474 --> 00:18:29,680
Just go.

315
00:18:34,981 --> 00:18:38,861
JOJO: Slowly, now. You don't
need that much, just half.

316
00:18:39,919 --> 00:18:42,798
Easy, easy.

317
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:46,033
You see, Ramon?

318
00:18:46,092 --> 00:18:48,663
One drop at a time, not all at
once like you did last week.

319
00:18:48,728 --> 00:18:49,798
No, I didn't.

320
00:18:49,862 --> 00:18:51,398
Don't contradict!

321
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:58,013
A man who sees his own
shortcomings and corrects them

322
00:18:58,070 --> 00:18:59,879
is on his way to meet God.

323
00:19:02,341 --> 00:19:04,844
Frankie, come help teach these boys.

324
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:08,825
Your mind isn't here.

325
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:14,388
You wanna be strong, you stay focused.

326
00:19:14,453 --> 00:19:16,126
You watch Bennie. He's focused.

327
00:19:16,188 --> 00:19:18,065
That's how he gets the job done.

328
00:19:18,124 --> 00:19:19,831
I got the job done, Jojo.

329
00:19:19,892 --> 00:19:23,203
Half done. Now I told you, watch Bennie.

330
00:19:33,239 --> 00:19:36,448
You see, Frankie? That's focus.

331
00:19:42,948 --> 00:19:45,121
Jamal's parents were supposed to contact us

332
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,891
to tell us where to send his school records,

333
00:19:46,952 --> 00:19:48,329
but we never heard from them.

334
00:19:48,387 --> 00:19:50,993
Jamal ever talk about working
in South Carolina?

335
00:19:51,057 --> 00:19:52,593
No, I never heard that.

336
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:54,729
Could we see other files from students

337
00:19:54,794 --> 00:19:57,240
who moved away in the last year or so?

338
00:19:57,296 --> 00:19:59,242
Sure. We keep them over here.

339
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:03,306
There's a notation in Jamal's
records from the school nurse.

340
00:20:03,369 --> 00:20:04,746
Two weeks before he moved,

341
00:20:04,804 --> 00:20:08,843
he showed up with a black eye
and a broken collar bone.

342
00:20:09,809 --> 00:20:11,015
Here you go.

343
00:20:19,819 --> 00:20:21,890
This one moved to Fresno, California.

344
00:20:21,954 --> 00:20:24,298
The school board confirms he's enrolled there.

345
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:28,598
Here, Christopher White,
broken arm six months ago.

346
00:20:28,661 --> 00:20:31,267
3 weeks later, his parents
say he moved to Oklahoma

347
00:20:31,664 --> 00:20:33,200
to live with relatives.

348
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:36,777
There's no confirmation in the file.

349
00:20:37,203 --> 00:20:39,308
We try to stay on top of things.

350
00:20:40,106 --> 00:20:41,380
Marco Reyes.

351
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,250
His parents say they sent him to
Mexico to live with his grandmother.

352
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,256
That was a week after he showed up for class

353
00:20:46,312 --> 00:20:48,314
with eight stitches in his face.

354
00:20:48,647 --> 00:20:52,094
These kids were all getting a
beating as a going-away present.

355
00:20:56,055 --> 00:20:57,864
Well, they have something else in common.

356
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:00,870
They were all from the same 12-block radius.

357
00:21:01,527 --> 00:21:03,939
The same 12 scared blocks.

358
00:21:08,167 --> 00:21:11,046
Some kids were trolling
for scrap metal last October

359
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:13,481
along I-95 near exit 43.

360
00:21:13,539 --> 00:21:15,644
Their dog started digging.

361
00:21:16,008 --> 00:21:18,318
John Doe, 12 to 13 years old.

362
00:21:18,577 --> 00:21:21,421
He matches one of the set of
dental records you sent around.

363
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:23,217
Christopher White.

364
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:25,656
The throat was cut.

365
00:21:25,718 --> 00:21:28,665
The laceration was deep, all
the way back to the vertebra.

366
00:21:28,721 --> 00:21:30,723
Almost took his head clean off.

367
00:21:31,223 --> 00:21:34,568
The way the body was posed in the grave,

368
00:21:34,627 --> 00:21:39,235
stretched out, hands crossed
over the front, feet together.

369
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,171
A proper burial.

370
00:21:42,034 --> 00:21:44,207
A sign of respect?

371
00:21:45,337 --> 00:21:47,749
I'm looking at Christopher
White's birth certificate.

372
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:51,050
His body was dumped less than a
mile from where he was born.

373
00:21:56,282 --> 00:21:59,855
And these spots on the
shoe, anyone test them?

374
00:22:05,257 --> 00:22:08,033
Other than coloring and tanning agents,

375
00:22:08,093 --> 00:22:09,731
all you got here is shoe leather.

376
00:22:09,795 --> 00:22:12,605
No trace of anything that would cause
it to crack and discolor like that.

377
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:17,171
Yeah. You know, when I was a
kid, I had leather mitts,

378
00:22:17,236 --> 00:22:19,147
all right, and then they would get cracked,

379
00:22:19,205 --> 00:22:21,685
you know, when they were wet and cold.

380
00:22:21,740 --> 00:22:24,243
Well, that's how leather
reacts when it's frozen.

381
00:22:25,845 --> 00:22:27,756
What about flash frozen?

382
00:22:27,913 --> 00:22:29,415
Sure, with dry ice.

383
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:31,017
But that leaves a residue.

384
00:22:33,552 --> 00:22:34,895
Liquid nitrogen?

385
00:22:35,254 --> 00:22:36,289
Sure.

386
00:22:37,122 --> 00:22:39,329
It evaporates, leaves no residue.

387
00:22:43,896 --> 00:22:46,376
Look, I

388
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,607
was wondering if you could run
this through your machine.

389
00:22:50,669 --> 00:22:53,377
I wiped it off the floor of a kid's bedroom.

390
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,610
Is that grease?

391
00:22:56,575 --> 00:22:57,952
You tell me.

392
00:22:58,544 --> 00:23:01,218
Submicron Teflon chips. Graphite.

393
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:04,261
Rare polymers. Friction modifiers.

394
00:23:05,184 --> 00:23:07,323
I'm afraid to ask you where
you put this kind of grease.

395
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:09,662
It's Italian racing bicycle grease.

396
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:11,633
It's $30 a tube.

397
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:15,561
I can imagine what the bicycles cost.

398
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:19,099
Up to $15,000.

399
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:24,544
If the Iberra kid had a bike
like this in his bedroom,

400
00:23:25,504 --> 00:23:27,541
it had to be stolen. That's what he was into.

401
00:23:27,606 --> 00:23:29,643
Yeah, that's what they're all into.

402
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:34,248
The kid in New Jersey, he dripped
liquid nitrogen on his shoe.

403
00:23:34,713 --> 00:23:37,455
Liquid nitrogen is used
to break bicycle locks.

404
00:23:37,516 --> 00:23:39,393
I pulled some figures from Compstat.

405
00:23:39,451 --> 00:23:41,727
There are $3 million worth of bicycles stolen

406
00:23:41,787 --> 00:23:43,460
in all five boroughs every year.

407
00:23:43,522 --> 00:23:45,729
Most of it involves adult perps,

408
00:23:45,791 --> 00:23:49,170
but there are reports of one gang
of kids operating in Manhattan.

409
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,366
They're quick, they use different MO's

410
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,034
and they've never been caught.

411
00:23:53,165 --> 00:23:54,769
And they're all well-trained.

412
00:23:55,334 --> 00:23:57,439
Like Jojo said, kids are like sponges.

413
00:23:57,503 --> 00:23:59,414
And I assume the ones that
don't make the grade

414
00:23:59,471 --> 00:24:01,041
or make trouble get their throats cut.

415
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:02,813
We matched up 3 of the missing boys,

416
00:24:02,875 --> 00:24:05,549
including Jamal Dupuis, with John Doe remains.

417
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:08,615
Their parents have been contacted,
but they're still not talking.

418
00:24:08,681 --> 00:24:10,957
DEAKINS: Let's be careful
how much we lean on them.

419
00:24:11,016 --> 00:24:14,486
According to the direction
of the marks on the vertebrae,

420
00:24:14,553 --> 00:24:18,626
these kids had their throats slit from behind

421
00:24:19,725 --> 00:24:22,228
from left to right.

422
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,967
The killer was right-handed.

423
00:24:24,029 --> 00:24:26,737
But Sami Iberra and his father

424
00:24:26,799 --> 00:24:30,645
had their throat cut from right to left.

425
00:24:30,703 --> 00:24:33,206
Their killer was left-handed.

426
00:24:38,377 --> 00:24:40,721
Jojo was breaking in someone new?

427
00:24:41,447 --> 00:24:44,360
Somebody who didn't quite do the job right.

428
00:24:46,118 --> 00:24:49,759
That's a Cielo with a set of record
10 shifters. Bennie got that.

429
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:52,735
Good work, Bennie. Real good work.

430
00:24:53,292 --> 00:24:56,068
You know what? You guys go home, okay?

431
00:24:56,128 --> 00:24:57,801
Frankie and I can take it from here.

432
00:24:57,863 --> 00:24:59,274
They could help unload.

433
00:24:59,331 --> 00:25:01,868
You don't look good. You eat lunch?

434
00:25:02,134 --> 00:25:05,445
I just haven't been sleeping
so good, that's all.

435
00:25:06,572 --> 00:25:07,846
I heard what the cops found.

436
00:25:07,906 --> 00:25:10,045
I know. But you're standing up good.

437
00:25:10,109 --> 00:25:12,385
Your loyalty, that's what's appreciated.

438
00:25:12,678 --> 00:25:14,055
Thanks, Jojo.

439
00:25:14,113 --> 00:25:16,753
"The power within stays safe
and free from assault,

440
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:19,352
"superior to pleasure and pain,
doing nothing randomly."

441
00:25:19,418 --> 00:25:21,159
- You remember that?
- I do.

442
00:25:21,220 --> 00:25:22,426
I know you do.

443
00:25:22,488 --> 00:25:25,128
And I know you're gonna
continue standing by everyone.

444
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,669
Your fellow warriors.

445
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:29,365
Any sacrifice that's needed.

446
00:25:29,728 --> 00:25:31,571
That's what I know you can do.

447
00:25:32,498 --> 00:25:34,102
Well, what do you mean?

448
00:25:34,933 --> 00:25:36,537
If it's necessary,

449
00:25:39,438 --> 00:25:41,816
we know you'll do what a man would do.

450
00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:48,590
"Don't act as if you're
going to live 10,000 years.

451
00:25:48,647 --> 00:25:49,955
"Death hangs over you.

452
00:25:50,983 --> 00:25:55,762
"While you live, while it's
in your power, be good."

453
00:26:00,125 --> 00:26:02,162
ANTHONY: Frankie's not home
a lot of the time.

454
00:26:02,661 --> 00:26:05,574
Look, is there a reward
for information or what?

455
00:26:06,432 --> 00:26:07,570
- A reward?
- Hmm.

456
00:26:07,633 --> 00:26:11,171
Maybe we can scrounge something
up. What do you think?

457
00:26:11,236 --> 00:26:14,217
$20 bucks. We can handle $20 bucks.

458
00:26:14,273 --> 00:26:15,547
$20 bucks?

459
00:26:16,075 --> 00:26:19,022
Well, it's not like he's on
the FBI's top 10 list.

460
00:26:23,949 --> 00:26:28,091
Well, I can see Frankie's Mom
has kept her youthful looks.

461
00:26:38,831 --> 00:26:41,869
Don't run, Frankie. It won't
be good for you if you run.

462
00:26:46,071 --> 00:26:47,175
I'm not running.

463
00:26:47,239 --> 00:26:48,479
What you go and do, you little jerk?

464
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:49,917
Bringing the cops into my house

465
00:26:49,975 --> 00:26:51,318
after all I've done for you.

466
00:26:51,410 --> 00:26:53,048
I hope they fry you.

467
00:26:54,279 --> 00:26:56,281
That's a good attitude, Frank.

468
00:26:56,982 --> 00:26:58,461
And so it begins.

469
00:27:01,954 --> 00:27:04,161
Your Dad's quite a ladies man, huh?

470
00:27:11,864 --> 00:27:13,901
When my Dad came home at night,

471
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:16,938
I could smell them on him.

472
00:27:19,171 --> 00:27:21,151
I was ashamed.

473
00:27:25,110 --> 00:27:27,386
Right? I mean, like your Dad.

474
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:33,129
I can see why you look up to Jojo.

475
00:27:33,685 --> 00:27:35,164
I really can.

476
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:37,496
"Everything has always been the same."

477
00:27:38,624 --> 00:27:39,796
How do you mean?

478
00:27:40,492 --> 00:27:43,371
"You can't lose another life
than the one you're living now,

479
00:27:43,929 --> 00:27:46,307
"or live another one
than the one you're losing.

480
00:27:47,132 --> 00:27:49,976
"The longest life is
the same as the shortest."

481
00:27:50,636 --> 00:27:52,138
What's he talking about?

482
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:56,046
"The longest life is
the same as the shortest."

483
00:27:56,441 --> 00:27:57,852
I know this.

484
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:08,161
"Some things are rushing into
existence. Others out of it."

485
00:28:10,489 --> 00:28:12,127
GOREN: Did you read this, Frankie?

486
00:28:12,191 --> 00:28:17,140
"Time is a river, a violent
current of events, glimpsed...

487
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:20,135
"Glimpsed..."

488
00:28:20,199 --> 00:28:23,908
"Glimpsed once, already
carried past us and is gone."

489
00:28:25,837 --> 00:28:26,838
Yeah.

490
00:28:27,406 --> 00:28:29,477
That's Marcus Aurelius.

491
00:28:29,741 --> 00:28:31,277
The dictates of a warrior.

492
00:28:32,010 --> 00:28:33,580
(GROANING)

493
00:28:40,586 --> 00:28:41,997
(GAGGING)

494
00:28:42,254 --> 00:28:43,255
Okay.

495
00:28:43,889 --> 00:28:47,166
Call EMS. He's taken something.
He's trying to kill himself.

496
00:28:47,226 --> 00:28:49,763
This is unit 229. We have
an attempted suicide.

497
00:28:49,828 --> 00:28:50,932
GOREN: What did you take, Frankie?

498
00:28:50,996 --> 00:28:54,239
I am a warrior. I welcome death.

499
00:28:54,299 --> 00:28:58,247
Yes, and warriors try to live.
They fight and they... And they live.

500
00:28:58,503 --> 00:29:00,449
The son of a bitch!

501
00:29:00,505 --> 00:29:03,577
He told him to do it! He told him to!

502
00:29:06,745 --> 00:29:08,782
He's on a respirator. It's touch and go.

503
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:12,021
He took some kind of cyanide. He must
have been carrying it around with him.

504
00:29:12,084 --> 00:29:13,392
In case of capture?

505
00:29:13,452 --> 00:29:15,659
What, did this boy step out
of, an old war movie?

