00:29:15,721 --> 00:29:17,462
An old Roman war movie.

507
00:29:17,522 --> 00:29:19,399
Before he went into convulsions,

508
00:29:19,458 --> 00:29:21,529
he was quoting Marcus Aurelius.

509
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:23,368
Marcus Aurelius? The Meditations.

510
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:26,875
He was a Roman emperor... and a
follower of the Roman Stoic philosophy.

511
00:29:26,932 --> 00:29:28,707
But I wasn't aware that Marcus Aurelius

512
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:30,769
was an advocate of suicide.

513
00:29:30,836 --> 00:29:32,042
Well, he wasn't.

514
00:29:32,571 --> 00:29:34,812
But like any belief system in the wrong hands,

515
00:29:34,873 --> 00:29:37,877
Stoicism can be twisted
to mean whatever you want.

516
00:29:37,943 --> 00:29:40,219
The wrong hands being Jojo Rios.

517
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:42,316
His idea of self-control.

518
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:49,421
The way that the bodies
were laid out for the burial,

519
00:29:49,488 --> 00:29:51,525
where they were buried,

520
00:29:52,658 --> 00:29:54,729
he's following the playbook.

521
00:29:55,394 --> 00:29:59,001
Even the name of his sound
studio, Sixteen-One.

522
00:29:59,298 --> 00:30:01,437
The year 161 AD,

523
00:30:02,134 --> 00:30:05,081
the year Marcus Aurelius was made emperor.

524
00:30:05,871 --> 00:30:08,545
Mr. Rios sees himself as a general?

525
00:30:09,308 --> 00:30:11,845
Leading 12-year-olds in
a criminal enterprise

526
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:14,720
with the help of a second century philosophy?

527
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:17,490
Stoicism inspired the Roman legions

528
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:19,426
to march across Europe and Africa.

529
00:30:19,484 --> 00:30:21,327
I mean, if you're gonna start a gang,

530
00:30:21,386 --> 00:30:22,763
you could pick a worse model.

531
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:26,496
Detectives, I'm sorry. The
Marino boy didn't make it.

532
00:30:27,092 --> 00:30:28,662
The doctor will be out to talk to you.

533
00:30:28,727 --> 00:30:31,230
I need to notify the next of kin. The father.

534
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:35,338
Nurse,

535
00:30:37,069 --> 00:30:40,516
his father, he's not gonna care.

536
00:30:44,476 --> 00:30:46,217
We need a gag order.

537
00:30:46,278 --> 00:30:47,916
I mean, the hospital can put out

538
00:30:47,979 --> 00:30:49,754
that we brought Frank Marino in,

539
00:30:49,815 --> 00:30:52,955
but we don't want them to
tell anyone that he's dead.

540
00:30:53,018 --> 00:30:54,019
We don't?

541
00:30:54,319 --> 00:30:56,765
No. If Frank Marino talked,

542
00:30:56,822 --> 00:30:59,894
we'd have a case against Jojo Rios.

543
00:31:01,159 --> 00:31:03,537
We need him to have talked.

544
00:31:03,595 --> 00:31:06,235
Excuse me, but I really
do need to notify the parents.

545
00:31:06,298 --> 00:31:09,142
Nurse, I'm Ronald Carver,

546
00:31:09,201 --> 00:31:10,908
Assistant District Attorney.

547
00:31:10,969 --> 00:31:12,846
I need to explain something to you.

548
00:31:13,238 --> 00:31:15,684
It's time to round up some legionnaires.

549
00:31:40,132 --> 00:31:41,304
Bennie, come on.

550
00:31:41,366 --> 00:31:43,039
I'm moving. I'm moving.

551
00:31:43,101 --> 00:31:44,375
Not anymore.

552
00:31:44,436 --> 00:31:45,437
Uh-oh.

553
00:31:47,672 --> 00:31:49,515
Jojo takes care of us.

554
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:52,145
No, see, that money he's
making off the bicycles,

555
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:54,588
he's not putting that in your college fund.

556
00:31:54,846 --> 00:31:57,725
He's gonna spend it while you sit in Spofford.

557
00:31:59,918 --> 00:32:02,990
Ramon, don't be a sucker!

558
00:32:03,989 --> 00:32:06,697
Your mom's all alone with
your two little brothers.

559
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:09,136
What are they gonna think if you go to jail?

560
00:32:09,194 --> 00:32:12,073
They'll see I'm a man. To stay true.

561
00:32:12,164 --> 00:32:15,338
That's what it means to be a man.

562
00:32:16,735 --> 00:32:20,410
GOREN: Christopher White, Marcos Reyes,

563
00:32:20,906 --> 00:32:25,082
Jamal Dupuis and Sami Iberra.

564
00:32:25,444 --> 00:32:27,287
What happened to them, Bennie?

565
00:32:28,079 --> 00:32:30,320
And why did Jojo have them killed?

566
00:32:30,849 --> 00:32:33,352
Listen, I do not know anything about that.

567
00:32:33,552 --> 00:32:36,192
What about Christopher White?
He was in your class.

568
00:32:36,254 --> 00:32:39,258
He must have done something
pretty bad to end up like this.

569
00:32:39,324 --> 00:32:42,271
What, was he weak? Disloyal?

570
00:32:42,327 --> 00:32:44,238
Did he steal from the others?

571
00:32:44,296 --> 00:32:45,866
Listen, he was a good person.

572
00:32:46,565 --> 00:32:47,805
He was a good person?

573
00:32:53,238 --> 00:32:54,239
Yeah.

574
00:32:54,873 --> 00:32:56,113
That's right.

575
00:32:58,310 --> 00:32:59,311
I forgot.

576
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:08,488
You don't speak ill of the dead.

577
00:33:10,222 --> 00:33:13,692
You don't speak ill of a fellow warrior.

578
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:15,498
Chris White was a fellow warrior.

579
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,699
He's buried in New Jersey,

580
00:33:19,130 --> 00:33:21,167
the land of his birth

581
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:31,085
because that's what Marcus
Aurelius told you to do.

582
00:33:35,514 --> 00:33:38,461
You see, we know all
about Jojo and Mr. Aurelius.

583
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:39,825
Frankie told us.

584
00:33:40,218 --> 00:33:43,358
Did you know that he was arrested earlier?

585
00:33:44,089 --> 00:33:46,899
If that had happened, he'd know what to do.

586
00:33:47,092 --> 00:33:48,435
He wouldn't just nark on Jojo.

587
00:33:48,493 --> 00:33:49,494
Oh, no.

588
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:55,500
No, he told us how him and
Jojo laid Chris in his grave.

589
00:33:56,067 --> 00:33:58,775
No. Frankie's a hero, just like Jojo.

590
00:33:59,137 --> 00:34:00,673
He would never turn his back on us.

591
00:34:00,739 --> 00:34:03,845
Jojo's a hero? How do you figure
that? He's a sound engineer.

592
00:34:03,909 --> 00:34:05,752
No, no. I know his story.

593
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:07,585
Jojo came from Cuba.

594
00:34:07,646 --> 00:34:09,523
His boat sank, and it was night.

595
00:34:10,148 --> 00:34:12,628
Everybody drowned except for Jojo.

596
00:34:13,552 --> 00:34:15,691
He made it because he's strong.

597
00:34:16,955 --> 00:34:18,525
He taught us how to be strong.

598
00:34:18,590 --> 00:34:20,069
- GOREN: To be true?
- Yes.

599
00:34:22,394 --> 00:34:24,032
He showed you by example.

600
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:26,765
You would never betray him

601
00:34:26,831 --> 00:34:28,833
because he would never betray you.

602
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,176
- Yes.
- BOTH: The way of the warrior.

603
00:34:41,346 --> 00:34:43,724
Well, it's nice to see kids
studying the classics.

604
00:34:43,782 --> 00:34:45,784
And learning all the wrong lessons.

605
00:34:45,850 --> 00:34:49,423
Well, should we pick up a few
more of Mr. Rios' disciples?

606
00:34:49,821 --> 00:34:51,095
Well, there's no point.

607
00:34:51,156 --> 00:34:53,534
I mean, we can't threaten them
with anything more potent

608
00:34:53,592 --> 00:34:55,230
than what they're already afraid of.

609
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:58,631
Afraid of falling short, as warriors, as men,

610
00:34:59,197 --> 00:35:01,677
in the eyes of their hero.

611
00:35:01,733 --> 00:35:04,077
All that's missing is
war paint and a bonfire.

612
00:35:04,135 --> 00:35:06,843
The wild place inside every boy's heart.

613
00:35:10,275 --> 00:35:13,017
You know, Jojo knows that...

614
00:35:13,979 --> 00:35:16,755
Well, he knows that every
good hero needs a good story.

615
00:35:18,216 --> 00:35:20,127
I need to call the INS.

616
00:35:24,189 --> 00:35:26,226
JOJO: I was going out to see
a client about a booking.

617
00:35:26,291 --> 00:35:28,328
- You're lucky you caught me.
- We're lucky that way.

618
00:35:28,393 --> 00:35:30,964
Well, we won't be long.
It's about Frank Marino.

619
00:35:31,029 --> 00:35:33,509
- What did you call him? Your apprentice?
- Yeah.

620
00:35:33,565 --> 00:35:35,602
Frankie's a good kid. I
hope he's not in trouble.

621
00:35:35,667 --> 00:35:36,702
Afraid so.

622
00:35:36,768 --> 00:35:39,476
We think he's mixed up with
a ring of bicycle thieves.

623
00:35:39,537 --> 00:35:40,811
That's hard to believe.

624
00:35:40,872 --> 00:35:42,852
GOREN: Well, what's worse is that

625
00:35:45,710 --> 00:35:48,213
when we were questioning
him, he did something,

626
00:35:49,848 --> 00:35:51,418
well, inexplicable.

627
00:35:52,283 --> 00:35:54,058
He took cyanide.

628
00:35:54,919 --> 00:35:56,057
My God, that's...

629
00:35:56,488 --> 00:35:57,489
He killed himself?

630
00:35:58,356 --> 00:35:59,630
GOREN: Well, no.

631
00:36:00,358 --> 00:36:01,359
He botched it.

632
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:03,168
He's still alive.

633
00:36:03,228 --> 00:36:04,866
He's at Methodist Hospital.

634
00:36:04,929 --> 00:36:07,375
We should be able to talk to him by tomorrow.

635
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:13,005
That's good. I'm glad he's gonna make it.

636
00:36:13,271 --> 00:36:14,579
EAMES: He might not be so glad.

637
00:36:14,639 --> 00:36:16,380
He's facing a couple murder charges

638
00:36:16,441 --> 00:36:18,921
for Sami Iberra and his father, Enrique.

639
00:36:18,977 --> 00:36:20,354
Yeah, he botched that, too.

640
00:36:21,379 --> 00:36:24,292
Yeah, I mean, I'm sure he wasn't
planning on Sami's father,

641
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:27,796
you know, running out of the
park with his throat slit.

642
00:36:28,219 --> 00:36:31,098
Look, I'd be surprised if Frankie
had anything to do with that.

643
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:35,664
But then again, I don't really
know what he does on his own time.

644
00:36:35,727 --> 00:36:39,174
Well, what he does is, I mean,
you know, besides heisting bikes

645
00:36:41,099 --> 00:36:42,271
and killing people...

646
00:36:42,333 --> 00:36:44,040
JOJO: On his own time.

647
00:36:44,135 --> 00:36:45,546
- Do you mind?
- GOREN: Sorry.

648
00:36:45,603 --> 00:36:47,082
JOJO: That's expensive equipment.

649
00:36:47,138 --> 00:36:48,947
Sure, sure. So sorry.

650
00:36:50,742 --> 00:36:52,949
What he does is he fills his mind

651
00:36:53,645 --> 00:36:57,354
with some kind of, you
know, martial philosophy

652
00:36:58,416 --> 00:37:02,330
about warriors and loyalty, accepting death.

653
00:37:03,088 --> 00:37:05,898
That's what he talked about
on the way to the hospital.

654
00:37:07,092 --> 00:37:08,935
You don't know anything about that?

655
00:37:09,461 --> 00:37:10,496
No.

656
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:13,736
That's funny because we thought
that it came from you,

657
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:16,335
you know, along with the protein bars.

658
00:37:16,735 --> 00:37:19,272
I mean, even if I did believe all that stuff,

659
00:37:20,572 --> 00:37:24,076
these are hard-core street kids, you know?

660
00:37:24,175 --> 00:37:26,553
I mean, they wouldn't listen to a guy like me.

661
00:37:26,611 --> 00:37:28,989
Come on, you're being too modest.

662
00:37:29,047 --> 00:37:30,253
These kids look up to you.

663
00:37:30,315 --> 00:37:31,453
Where did you hear that from?

664
00:37:31,516 --> 00:37:34,554
Bennie Renato. He thinks you're a hero.

665
00:37:36,855 --> 00:37:39,461
That's crazy. You know, these are street kids.

666
00:37:39,524 --> 00:37:41,060
They're running a con on you.

667
00:37:41,559 --> 00:37:45,939
Well, no, I mean, Bennie,
he seemed very sincere.

668
00:37:47,532 --> 00:37:51,446
Hey, he told us about your
perilous crossing from Cuba.

669
00:37:54,105 --> 00:37:57,382
You know, your boat sank at
night. Everyone drowned.

670
00:37:57,709 --> 00:37:59,086
I mean, except you.

671
00:37:59,611 --> 00:38:01,557
That's right. I told him that. So what?

672
00:38:01,613 --> 00:38:03,286
Why, because it's true, right?

673
00:38:03,414 --> 00:38:04,620
Of course.

674
00:38:04,682 --> 00:38:06,423
It was the Mariel boat lift.

675
00:38:07,418 --> 00:38:09,227
It was when Castro emptied his jails.

676
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:10,891
You came over with your father.

677
00:38:13,792 --> 00:38:15,294
Your father is a convicted rapist.

678
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:16,634
That's a lie.

679
00:38:16,728 --> 00:38:19,641
Hey, not according to your INS file.

680
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:24,406
Your boat, well, it didn't sink.

681
00:38:26,404 --> 00:38:31,114
And those people, nobody was lost at sea or...

682
00:38:33,678 --> 00:38:37,182
The INS put your father
in a detention center.

683
00:38:37,282 --> 00:38:38,818
They put you in a foster home

684
00:38:38,883 --> 00:38:41,989
and then in a group home until you were 17.

685
00:38:42,620 --> 00:38:44,793
Okay. Okay.

686
00:38:46,591 --> 00:38:47,899
Sol made up a story.

687
00:38:47,959 --> 00:38:49,905
Well, not just any story.

688
00:38:50,528 --> 00:38:52,769
Well, it was, you know, a hero's story.

689
00:38:52,831 --> 00:38:55,471
I mean, you know, the child
being plucked from the water.

690
00:38:55,533 --> 00:38:58,104
That's Moses with a little
Jonah thrown in there.

691
00:38:58,436 --> 00:39:00,848
And then the orphan who grows
up to be a great leader.

692
00:39:00,905 --> 00:39:05,081
That's Marcus Aurelius.

693
00:39:06,578 --> 00:39:07,886
You know what?

694
00:39:11,883 --> 00:39:13,590
I don't know what you're talking about.

695
00:39:13,651 --> 00:39:17,929
No? Marcus Aurelius. That warrior's creed?

696
00:39:18,756 --> 00:39:21,168
That loyalty unto death stuff?

697
00:39:23,962 --> 00:39:25,066
You taught them that.

698
00:39:25,129 --> 00:39:26,130
No.

699
00:39:27,498 --> 00:39:29,136
Look, I was new in the neighborhood.

700
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,736
I had to make nice with the locals,

701
00:39:30,802 --> 00:39:32,509
so I let their kids hang out here. That's all.

702
00:39:32,570 --> 00:39:35,244
Oh, that's good for PR, I guess.

703
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:36,307
I swear to God.

704
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:39,753
And if I told them stories, Boy
Scout crap, it was just talk.

705
00:39:39,811 --> 00:39:41,757
All that stuff about loyalty was just talk?

706
00:39:41,813 --> 00:39:43,520
Loyalty's fine as far as it goes,

707
00:39:43,581 --> 00:39:46,721
but if Frankie and Bennie did something
illegal, that's not my responsibility.

708
00:39:46,784 --> 00:39:49,697
And if they're telling you something
different, they're liars.

709
00:39:51,289 --> 00:39:55,362
So, you gave them some attention

710
00:39:55,426 --> 00:39:58,202
and a little advice and
sent them on their way.

711
00:39:58,263 --> 00:39:59,435
That's all I did.

712
00:39:59,497 --> 00:40:04,207
And if they got into trouble, you know,
themselves, they were on their own.

713
00:40:04,269 --> 00:40:05,748
I don't owe them a thing.

714
00:40:08,506 --> 00:40:09,678
Not even loyalty?

715
00:40:11,509 --> 00:40:12,510
Nothing.

716
00:40:14,946 --> 00:40:18,120
All right, Mr. Rios, I think
we've wasted enough of your time

717
00:40:18,182 --> 00:40:19,627
talking about these punks.

718
00:40:25,590 --> 00:40:26,694
What are you doing?

719
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:28,203
Did you take that CD out of there?

720
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:30,569
- Hey man, the thing just popped out.
- Yeah, the hell it did.

721
00:40:34,966 --> 00:40:36,172
You recorded me.

722
00:40:37,068 --> 00:40:38,604
You son of a bitch recorded me.

723
00:40:38,670 --> 00:40:39,705
What's the big deal? It's not like...

724
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:41,011
Now, you can't take that!

725
00:40:42,607 --> 00:40:44,985
That's my property, now you give it to me.

726
00:40:51,549 --> 00:40:54,086
What did you think you were
gonna do with this, huh?

727
00:40:54,385 --> 00:40:55,887
I was gonna use it

728
00:40:55,954 --> 00:40:59,458
to see if any of the kids had illusions
about how you felt about them.

729
00:41:00,024 --> 00:41:02,004
I told you, those dumb kids

730
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:04,165
have got nothing to do with me.

731
00:41:14,172 --> 00:41:15,674
I'm surprised at you, Jojo.

732
00:41:16,174 --> 00:41:17,175
About what?

733
00:41:17,408 --> 00:41:22,016
Well, I mean, a guy like you on the cutting
edge of sound recording technology,

734
00:41:23,214 --> 00:41:26,684
you know, thinking that we would
resort to using a synthesizer

735
00:41:27,018 --> 00:41:28,361
to bug your sound studio.

736
00:41:28,419 --> 00:41:30,956
Especially when we have neat stuff like this.

737
00:41:31,022 --> 00:41:34,526
An omni-directional microphone
and transmitter all in one.

738
00:41:34,592 --> 00:41:37,869
You know, that broadcasts
theater-quality sound

739
00:41:37,929 --> 00:41:41,206
through brick and soundproofing

740
00:41:42,367 --> 00:41:45,712
up to 100 yards away.

741
00:41:52,210 --> 00:41:54,486
You know, I can't believe you, Jojo.

742
00:41:54,846 --> 00:41:56,587
You know, I'm so stupid.

743
00:41:56,647 --> 00:41:58,092
What you think you heard,

744
00:41:58,483 --> 00:41:59,689
it was a trick.

745
00:41:59,751 --> 00:42:01,560
Listen, I heard, all right?

746
00:42:01,886 --> 00:42:03,058
So tell me, Jojo,

747
00:42:04,255 --> 00:42:05,598
what do we do now?

748
00:42:06,457 --> 00:42:09,370
To be true. What, do we be like Frankie?

749
00:42:10,895 --> 00:42:13,705
Tell me, what do we do to stay true?

750
00:42:18,403 --> 00:42:20,713
Yeah. I just want to tell them everything.

751
00:42:20,772 --> 00:42:21,773
Don't you dare!

752
00:42:21,839 --> 00:42:24,115
Jojo Rios, you're under arrest for murder.

753
00:42:24,175 --> 00:42:26,587
No, no, no. Bennie, Bennie,
Bennie! Listen to me.

754
00:42:26,644 --> 00:42:28,885
Listen to me! Listen.

755
00:42:30,314 --> 00:42:32,453
Listen, you're not stupid, Bennie.

756
00:42:32,884 --> 00:42:34,386
You're not stupid.

757
00:42:34,752 --> 00:42:36,925
You're a strong kid. You're a true kid.

